data.content:
**No Thread.Abort migration is needed here.**

Your code only uses `Thread.Start`, `Thread.Join`, and `Thread.Sleep` — none of which are affected by the .NET Framework → .NET 8 migration. These APIs work identically in modern .NET. There are no calls to `Thread.Abort`, no `ThreadAbortException` catch blocks, no `Thread.ResetAbort`, and no `Thread.Interrupt`. This code will compile and run correctly as-is on .NET 8.

**Optional modernization (unrelated to Thread.Abort):** You could replace the manual `Thread` usage with `Parallel.ForEach` or `Task.Run` for cleaner code:

```csharp
public async Task RunBatchAsync(List<WorkItem> items)
{
    await Parallel.ForEachAsync(items, async (item, ct) =>
    {
        await Task.Delay(100, ct); // replaces Thread.Sleep
        item.Result = ComputeResult(item.Input);
    });
}
```

This is purely a modernization choice — your existing code requires zero changes to work on .NET 8.
